**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
Currently the output is `IDisposableReadOnlyCollection<DisposableNamedOnnxValue>` and `NamedOnnxValue` provides:

```C#
        public IEnumerable<T> AsEnumerable<T>();
        public Tensor<T> AsTensor<T>();
```

In order to get a `float[]` result I can do either:

```C#
            using (var results = _session.Run(inputs))
            {
                return results.First().AsTensor<float>().ToDenseTensor().Buffer.ToArray();
            }
```

or use more `Linq` like

```C#
            using (var results = _session.Run(inputs))
            {
                return results.First().AsEnumerable<float>().ToArray();
            }
```

The latter is faster! 

**System information**
- ONNX Runtime version (you are using): 0.3.0

**Describe the solution you'd like**

Provide 

```C#
        public T[] AsArray<T>();
```

To directly get the array, I know my network outputs a contiguous array.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**

Alternative [Tensor types](https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/540) that may have easier way to get array.

**Additional context**
[This issue](https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/673) is related.

